A N A C T
RELATING TO HEALTH AND SAFETY -- VITAL RECORDS
Introduced By: Representatives Felix, Craven, Knight, McEntee, Dawson, Batista, Cruz,
Potter, Ajello, and Place
Date Introduced: February 07, 2025
Referred To: House Judiciary
(Dept. of Corrections)
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 23-3 of the General Laws entitled "Vital Records" is hereby amended
2 by adding thereto the following section:
3 23-3-25.2. Incarcerated persons' exemption for fees for copies and searches.
4 Any incarcerated person who is set to be released from prison to re-enter the community
5 shall be processed without a charge or fee when making a first request for vital statistics at the
6 department of health regarding a request for their own personal records.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
